<p>The building spawning is also done in the same system with an added radius for the buildings to spawn outside the Resource Area spawning radius. Inside the buildings, Resource Areas will also randomly spawn. Each building is a blueprint that has box collisions to determine where Resource Areas will spawn. The type of resource spawned in the buildings can be tweaked as well. It is determined by a range of the resource amount. The number of Resource Areas being spawned in the buildings can also be tweaked. The buildings only spawn once for now as I ran out of time. It would have been great if the buildings do spawn more if you wander far away enough from the cluster of buildings so it really feels like there are more to explore. There are only two types of buildings at the moment but more could easily be added by duplicating one of the building blueprints and changing the mesh and variables depending on what we want. The only time consuming process would be adding the box components for resource area spawning.</p>
